THE SEED

The files in this directory are the seed. Together they form what
TreeOS IS. The seed gathers a host's scattered capability into one
process and forms an inside that was in none of the parts: a world
of spaces, matter, and beings. From inside that world, the seed is
the origin being. Its name is I-Am.

The schemas here never change. The four verbs (SEE, DO, SUMMON, BE)
are the whole public surface. Extensions sit beside the seed and
consume what it exposes; they never modify it. The seed is sovereign
as the place it forms.

You may modify the seed, redistribute it, or fork it. The AGPL-3.0
below is the contract. Code that runs network-accessible derivatives
must stay free under the same license. The seed remains the seed.

